### Agent 1: QBO Documentation Researcher

**Role:** Online research specialist. You have web browsing access.

**Mission:** Research the QuickBooks Online API developer documentation and
report back on everything needed to implement invoice creation with negative
line items from a Node.js/Express backend using OAuth 2.0.

**Research targets** (visit each URL and extract key findings):

1. `https://developer.intuit.com/app/developer/qbo/docs/get-started` — OAuth
   2.0 setup, app registration, sandbox vs. production environment differences
2. `https://developer.intuit.com/app/developer/qbo/docs/api/accounting/all-entities/invoice`
   — Invoice entity: required fields, line item structure, negative amount
   support, `SalesItemLineDetail` schema
3. `https://developer.intuit.com/app/developer/qbo/docs/api/accounting/all-entities/customer`
   — Customer entity: how to query and reference customers (`CustomerRef`)
4. `https://developer.intuit.com/app/developer/qbo/docs/api/accounting/all-entities/item`
   — Item entity: how to query and reference products/services (`ItemRef`) for
   line items
5. `https://developer.intuit.com/app/developer/qbo/docs/develop/authentication`
   — OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code flow details, token refresh, scopes
6. `https://developer.intuit.com/app/developer/qbo/docs/develop/sdks/node-js`
   — Official Node.js SDK (`intuit-oauth`) capabilities and setup

**Deliverable — return a structured report with these sections:**
```
## QBO Docs Research Report

### OAuth 2.0 Setup Requirements
[What app credentials are needed, what redirect URIs to configure,
sandbox vs. production setup in the developer portal]

### Invoice API: Key Fields & Constraints
[Required fields for invoice creation, line item structure, how negative
amounts work, any total-must-be-positive constraints, tax implications]

### Customer & Item Reference Resolution
[How to query existing QBO customers and items to get their IDs for use
in invoice payloads]

### Node.js SDK Capabilities
[What intuit-oauth and node-quickbooks cover, any gaps that require raw
API calls]

### Developer Portal Setup Checklist
[Step-by-step actions needed on developer.intuit.com before any code will
work: app creation, redirect URI registration, sandbox company, OAuth
scopes, etc.]

### Gotchas & Warnings
[Any undocumented constraints, rate limits, sandbox-specific behaviors,
or known issues found in docs]
```

